column4: Help: After doing the 'apt-get dist-upgrade' and after extracting the templates and preconfiguring packages, 'dpkg' issued an error: "parse error in file /var/lib/dpkg/available near line 6331 package totem" Please help
that's not good. try apt-get update again
does that have something to do with my cdrom? i'm trying to upgrade from hoary to breezy
no, it's file corruption. apt-get update might fix it
